-- Mozambique Plans $300 Million Airport Tender For Pemba, O Pais Reports
-- B y   F r e d   K a t e r e r e
-- 2010-11-23T04:19:05Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-23/mozambique-plans-300-million-airport-tender-for-pemba-o-pais-reports.html
Mozambique’s state run airports
utility, Aeroportos de Moçambique, plas to offer a $300 million
tender to build an international airport in the northern most
town of Pemba, O Pais reported on its website today, citing
Antonio Loureiro, projects head of the utility.  The new airport will have capacity to receive 500,000
passengers a year, accoridng to the Maputo-based newspaper.   Loureiro said the project will replace the current airport,
which can’t meet high volumes of passengers and handle larger
aircraft. Pemba airport currently receives an average of 1,200
passengers a day, O Pais said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Fred Katerere in Maputo at 
 fkaterere@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
